# One JSON object per line.
# Fields: question, answer, tags (optional)
# {"question":"sample question","answer":"sample answer","tags":["custom","priority"]}
{"question":"after deploy do I need to do anything before investors can see my presale","answer":"Yes — pay the listing fee! After deploying your presale appears in My Launches with a 'Pending' badge and a Pay Listing Fee button. Until you pay that fee your presale is NOT publicly visible. Go pay it ASAP.","tags":["listing_fee","presale","creator","visibility"]}
{"question":"after depositing 100000 point 9 remains unlocked what does this show","answer":"It shows post-deploy remaining wallet balance and its supply percentage used for limit enforcement.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","tokenomics","deploy"]}
{"question":"after finalization can I do anything else from my launch page","answer":"The sale is done after finalization. No more creator actions needed. The owner panel might still show for your reference but there's nothing more to do. LP is locked, tokens are claimable.","tags":["finalization","creator","lp_lock"]}
{"question":"after I create a token where do I find the contract address","answer":"It shows on the success screen right after deployment. Copy it and save it — you'll need it for creating your presale. You can also find it in your wallet transaction history or on the block explorer.","tags":["token_creation","contract_address","creator","support"]}
{"question":"after I finalize what happens to tokens that weren't sold","answer":"Liquidity is added using the presale token allocation + liquidity % of raised funds. Tokens beyond that go back to the creator (or can be burned depending on setup). Important: don't manually move tokens before finalization.","tags":["finalization","unsold_tokens","creator","liquidity"]}
{"question":"after I finalize when can investors actually claim their tokens","answer":"Immediately after your finalization txn is confirmed on-chain. The claim button appears on the investor's side within a few seconds via on-chain polling. They don't need to refresh.","tags":["finalization","investor","claim","creator"]}
{"question":"anon dev instant red flag or nah","answer":"Anonymous teams increase uncertainty. Treat as higher risk unless strong verifiable trust signals exist.","tags":["risk","security","investor","kyc"]}
{"question":"any final tips before I launch my presale on moonsale","answer":"Top 10 tips: 1) Get KYC first. 2) Lock team tokens before going live. 3) Set realistic softcap. 4) Lock liquidity 180+ days (365 for max score). 5) Fill ALL project info. 6) Finalize IMMEDIATELY after sale ends. 7) For fair launch size token pool carefully. 8) Don't set max contribution too high. 9) Never transfer unsold tokens before finalization. 10) Pay listing fee right after deploy — you're invisible until you do.","tags":["creator","onboarding","checklist","tips","launch"]}
{"question":"are fees different on BNB vs Ethereum","answer":"Yes. Fee amounts are set per chain by admin and can differ. ETH chain fees are typically higher (to match ETH value). Always check the current fee for your specific chain in the create form.","tags":["fees","bnb","ethereum","creator"]}
{"question":"are there any hidden fees I should know about","answer":"Moonsale states 'no hidden fees' — all fees visible on tool pages and in create forms before you deploy. The main surprise for new devs is the listing fee that comes AFTER deployment. Remember: deploy → then pay listing fee → then go public.","tags":["fees","creator","listing_fee","transparency"]}
{"question":"as a fair launch creator can I contribute to my own sale","answer":"Technically the contract allows anyone to contribute including the creator. But it's frowned upon as it manipulates the price. Be transparent with your community about this.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","price_manipulation","trust"]}
{"question":"audit badge means contract is safe","answer":"Audit badge is a positive signal, not a guarantee. Market and team risks can still exist.","tags":["audit","badge","security","risk"]}
{"question":"audit gives 5 points, do I need to get my token audited or just the moonsale platform contracts","answer":"Your project's smart contract. Get an external audit from a reputable firm, then submit the report link through /kyc-audit. Admin adds the badge with your report link. Moonsale's own platform contracts are separately audited.","tags":["audit","security_score","creator","kyc"]}
{"question":"blacklist detection no blacklist found meaning","answer":"No blacklist behavior was detected in the scan context.","tags":["scanner","security","token","creator"]}
{"question":"bro can u send me step by step how to invest","answer":"1) Open sale page. 2) Connect wallet on correct chain. 3) Enter amount within limits. 4) Confirm tx. 5) Claim after finalization.","tags":["investor","how_it_works","presale","fair_launch"]}
{"question":"bro cliff means what exactly","answer":"Cliff is the waiting period before additional vesting unlocks begin.","tags":["cliff","vesting","investor"]}
{"question":"bro how much minimum i can invest","answer":"Minimum contribution is set per sale and enforced on-chain. Check the sale panel for exact min buy.","tags":["contribution","investor","presale","fair_launch"]}
{"question":"bro i clicked buy and metamask showed error wht do i do","answer":"Check correct chain, available gas, and min/max limits. Retry transaction and inspect explorer error reason. If still failing, share tx hash with support.","tags":["metamask","wallet","support","contribution"]}
{"question":"bro i created token but made mistake in supply can i redeploy","answer":"Token parameters are usually immutable after deployment. In many cases you need to deploy a new token contract.","tags":["token_create","contracts","creator","support"]}
{"question":"bro i have usdt can i use that or only bnb eth","answer":"Contribution asset depends on sale design. Most native-chain launches use BNB on BNB Chain or ETH on Ethereum.","tags":["contribution","bnb","ethereum","investor"]}
{"question":"bro i joined fair launch early will i get better price or same as everyone","answer":"In standard fair launch, contributors settle with the same final pricing formula. Early entry does not guarantee a separate fixed tier.","tags":["fair_launch","price_discovery","investor"]}
{"question":"bro i paid listing fee but presale still not showing publicly","answer":"Check listing-fee transaction confirmation and allow indexing refresh. If still hidden, contact support with sale link and tx hash.","tags":["listing_fee","status","support","creator"]}
{"question":"bro i want out before sale ends can i withdraw","answer":"If early withdrawal is enabled, you can exit during Live phase, usually with a penalty.","tags":["withdraw","penalty","investor","presale","fair_launch"]}
{"question":"bro price in presale is different from price after listing why","answer":"Presale and listing prices can differ based on launch setup and liquidity configuration.","tags":["presale","liquidity","tokenomics","investor"]}
{"question":"bro the dev dmd me saying send bnb for whitelist is that real","answer":"Do not send funds through DMs. Only contribute via official MoonSale sale pages.","tags":["security","whitelist","risk","investor"]}
{"question":"bro total fees to launch a presale roughly how much in bnb","answer":"Total cost equals listing fee plus gas and optional tool fees. Check official fees page for current amounts.","tags":["fees","listing_fee","creator","bnb"]}
{"question":"bro transaction pending for 20min is it stuck","answer":"Pending often means congestion or low gas. Check explorer and use speed-up or cancel in wallet if available.","tags":["wallet","metamask","support","contribution"]}
{"question":"can a fair launch have both a whitelist phase and a public phase","answer":"Yes — start with whitelist enabled, then remove the whitelist mid-sale to open to public. You manage the whitelist from your sale page so you can toggle it during the sale.","tags":["fair_launch","whitelist","creator","phases"]}
{"question":"can dev cancel fair launch after it starts","answer":"Cancellation behavior depends on contract conditions and current sale state.","tags":["fair_launch","cancel","contracts","investor"]}
{"question":"can I add vesting to a fair launch like a presale has","answer":"No. Fair launches don't support built-in investor vesting. All tokens are claimable at once after finalization. If you need vesting for your own allocation use the separate Token Vesting tool at /vesting.","tags":["fair_launch","vesting","creator"]}
{"question":"can I bring an external token that wasn't made on moonsale","answer":"Yes you can use any ERC-20 token address. But if it wasn't deployed through Moonsale's factory it might not be auto-verified on the block explorer, which means your Contract Verified check on Security Score could fail and cost you 8 pts.","tags":["token","external_token","security_score","contract_verified","creator"]}
{"question":"can i bypass token eligibility scan","answer":"No. Blocking eligibility checks must pass before deployment.","tags":["scanner","security","creator","fair_launch"]}
{"question":"can I cancel a presale that already has contributions","answer":"Yes you can cancel even with contributions. Cancelling triggers the refund flow — investors can claim full refunds from the contract directly. You also get your deposited tokens back. Note: listing fee is not refunded.","tags":["cancel","presale","creator","refund","listing_fee"]}
{"question":"can I cancel a vesting schedule if something goes wrong","answer":"No. Vesting schedules on Moonsale are NON-REVOCABLE by design. Once created, neither you (creator) nor Moonsale can cancel or modify it. This is enforced at the smart contract level. The beneficiary is guaranteed to receive tokens per the schedule.","tags":["vesting","creator","immutable","support"]}
{"question":"can I cancel after hardcap is hit but before I finalized","answer":"Yes! This was specifically added as a recovery path if something goes wrong between hardcap being hit and finalization. You can cancel even a Filled presale. Investors get full refunds.","tags":["cancel","hardcap","presale","creator","refund","support"]}
{"question":"can I change max contribution during an active presale","answer":"No. Core settings like min/max contribution are locked after deployment. Plan carefully.","tags":["presale","creator","immutable","contribution","support"]}
{"question":"can I change my presale settings after deploying","answer":"Most settings like start/end time and price CANNOT be changed after deploy. Double-check everything before confirming. You can add/remove whitelist addresses after deploy, and pay the listing fee anytime. But core settings are locked on-chain.","tags":["presale","creator","settings","support","immutable"]}
{"question":"can I change which DEX my liquidity goes to during finalization","answer":"No. DEX is determined by chain — PancakeSwap for BSC, Uniswap for ETH. No option to change this.","tags":["dex","finalization","creator","liquidity"]}
{"question":"can i continue fair launch with optional fields empty","answer":"Yes for optional fields, but complete and verified project info is strongly recommended.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","listing"]}
{"question":"can i contribute from exchange wallet like binance directly","answer":"Not recommended. Use a self-custody wallet you control for contributions and claims.","tags":["wallet","security","investor","support"]}
{"question":"can I create vesting for someone else's wallet","answer":"Yes! The beneficiary field in the vesting form can be any wallet address — your own or someone else's (team member, advisor). The beneficiary sees the schedule in their own My Schedules dashboard.","tags":["vesting","creator","beneficiary"]}
{"question":"can I customize colors in the tokenomics creator","answer":"Yes! Each row has a color swatch you can click to change that category's color on the donut chart.","tags":["tokenomics_creator","creator","ui","tools"]}
{"question":"can I deploy an ERC-20 token on BSC and ETH from the same form","answer":"No, each token creation tx is network-specific. Switch your wallet to the chain you want and the form creates on that chain. Do it twice (once per chain) if you want tokens on both networks.","tags":["token_creation","chains","bnb","ethereum","creator"]}
{"question":"can I do a presale in USDT instead of BNB","answer":"No. Presales on BSC are denominated in BNB, and ETH on Ethereum. USDT contributions are not supported on Moonsale currently.","tags":["presale","usdt","bnb","creator","support"]}
{"question":"can i edit fair launch config after deploy","answer":"No, deploy creates immutable on-chain sale config. Reconfigure before deploy if changes are needed.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","deploy","contracts"]}
{"question":"can I edit my project description after deploying","answer":"Some metadata might be updateable — check your sale page owner panel for any edit options. Core on-chain settings like price/softcap/hardcap are not editable, but project description/socials might have an update option in the UI.","tags":["presale","creator","project_info","support"]}
{"question":"can I enable whitelist on a fair launch","answer":"Yes! Same as presale — toggle whitelist in the create form. After deployment you manage the whitelist from your fair launch page. Good for early access rounds before public.","tags":["fair_launch","whitelist","creator"]}
{"question":"can I exclude my presale contract from trading fees on a liquidity generator token","answer":"Yes. Through Token Management you can add addresses to the fee exclusion list. The presale contract address can be excluded so contributions don't incur trading fees.","tags":["token_management","liquidity_generator","creator","fees","presale"]}
{"question":"can i extend liquidity lock during active fair launch","answer":"No. During active live mode lock extension is not available. Finalize first, then adjust lock if supported.","tags":["liquidity","lock","fair_launch","creator"]}
{"question":"can i extend liquidity lock now my presale is running and in live mode","answer":"Once a presale or fair launch contract is deployed and Live, liquidity lock cannot be extended during live mode. Extend only after finalization.","tags":["liquidity","lock","presale","fair_launch","creator"]}
{"question":"can I finalize a fair launch that didn't hit softcap","answer":"No. If softcap isn't reached, you cannot finalize — the sale is failed. Investors get refunds and you get tokens back. No DEX listing happens.","tags":["fair_launch","softcap","finalization","refund","creator"]}
{"question":"can I have multiple presales for the same token","answer":"Technically yes since it's permissionless. But it looks weird to investors having multiple active presales for one token. Better to plan your raise amount correctly upfront.","tags":["presale","creator","multiple_presales"]}
{"question":"can I have multiple separate locks for the same token","answer":"Yes. Each lock is a separate record with its own unlock date, amount, and title. You can create multiple locks for different allocations (team, marketing, advisors etc) and each gets its own shareable detail page.","tags":["token_lock","creator","multiple_locks"]}
{"question":"can i invest 2 times in same presale or only once","answer":"Usually yes, multiple contributions are allowed while sale is Live, as long as your total stays within max limit.","tags":["contribution","investor","presale"]}
{"question":"can i launch fair launch if dex pair already has liquidity","answer":"No, not until that existing liquidity condition is resolved.","tags":["fair_launch","liquidity","dex","creator"]}
{"question":"can I launch on both BNB and ETH at the same time","answer":"Not in a single presale — each sale is on one chain. But you can create separate presales on each chain if you want. A token created on one chain can't be used on the other, so you'd need separate tokens too.","tags":["chains","bnb","ethereum","presale","creator"]}
{"question":"can I lock LP tokens using the moonsale token lock tool","answer":"Yes. LP tokens (like PancakeSwap LP tokens) can be locked using the Token Lock tool just like regular tokens. LP gets locked automatically at presale finalization too — the lock tool is for any additional manual locks you want.","tags":["token_lock","lp_lock","creator","liquidity"]}
{"question":"can I lock tokens before I deploy my presale","answer":"Yes. Token Lock is completely independent of presales. You can lock team tokens before, during, or after your presale. Actually doing it BEFORE launch and sharing the lock URL is great for building trust pre-launch.","tags":["token_lock","presale","creator","trust"]}
{"question":"can I lock tokens without having an active presale","answer":"Yes completely. Token Lock and Vesting tools are standalone — no presale needed. You can lock any ERC-20 token from any project or for any reason.","tags":["token_lock","vesting","creator","tools"]}
{"question":"can I negotiate fees with moonsale","answer":"No. Fees are set by platform admin and apply equally to all projects. No custom deals or discounts visible.","tags":["fees","creator","platform"]}
{"question":"can I rename my token symbol after launch","answer":"You can't. Token name and symbol are set at deployment and are immutable on-chain. Pick carefully before deploying.","tags":["token_creation","immutable","creator","support"]}
{"question":"can I run a presale without paying the listing fee and see who tries to invest","answer":"No. Until the listing fee is paid your presale page exists but is not on the public listings. No one can find it unless they have the direct URL. Pay the fee to go public.","tags":["listing_fee","presale","creator","visibility"]}
{"question":"can I see who locked tokens for a specific project even if I'm not the creator","answer":"The Security tab on any presale/fair launch page shows team token locks with 'View Lock' buttons linking to the lock detail pages. Anyone can view these without connecting a wallet.","tags":["token_lock","investor","verification","trust"]}
{"question":"can I set a custom DEX or only PancakeSwap and Uniswap","answer":"Currently it's fixed — PancakeSwap on BSC and Uniswap on ETH. There's no option to specify a different DEX.","tags":["dex","pancakeswap","uniswap","presale","creator"]}
{"question":"can I set a softcap on a fair launch","answer":"Yes. Softcap is required. If total raised doesn't hit softcap by end time, the sale fails and everyone gets refunded. Set a realistic softcap you can hit.","tags":["fair_launch","softcap","creator","refund"]}
{"question":"can I set a whitelist on my presale","answer":"Yes. In the create form there's an optional whitelist toggle. Enable it and after deployment you manage the whitelist from your presale page — add/remove wallet addresses at any time before the sale ends. Only whitelisted wallets can contribute.","tags":["whitelist","presale","creator"]}
{"question":"can I set different buy and sell fees on a liquidity generator token","answer":"Yes. Through the Token Management page you can configure buy fee and sell fee separately, and control how that fee is split between auto-liquidity and the marketing wallet.","tags":["token_management","liquidity_generator","fees","creator"]}
{"question":"can I set different contribution limits for different wallets like VIP tiers","answer":"Not directly through the presale settings — there's one global min and max. For tiered access you'd need to manage it through the whitelist (run whitelist phase first, then open public) but you can't set different max contributions per wallet tier.","tags":["presale","whitelist","contribution","creator","tiers"]}
{"question":"can i set unlocked tokens above platform limit","answer":"No. Deployment is blocked if post-deposit unlocked amount exceeds platform threshold.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","security","tokenomics"]}
{"question":"can I transfer a lock to another wallet","answer":"The lock is tied to the locked tokens and unlock date — the tokens can only be claimed by the wallet that created the lock (or beneficiary for vesting). Transfers of lock ownership are not a built-in feature.","tags":["token_lock","creator","support"]}
{"question":"can I transfer token ownership to another wallet after creating","answer":"The token generator deploys the contract with your wallet as owner. Standard ERC-20 ownership transfer depends on whether the contract has an ownerTransfer function — for Liquidity Generator and Mintable types it should, but check the contract. Standard type has no owner needed after deploy basically.","tags":["token","ownership","creator","token_management"]}
{"question":"can i use a fresh token without existing pair to pass eligibility","answer":"Yes, a token without an already-liquid pair avoids that specific DEX-reserve blocking condition.","tags":["fair_launch","token","liquidity","scanner","creator"]}
{"question":"can I use a multisig wallet to deploy and manage my presale","answer":"Technically possible if your multisig supports the required tx types, but the UI is designed for standard Web3 wallets. WalletConnect might work with some multisig setups. Test on testnet first.","tags":["wallet","multisig","presale","creator","support"]}
{"question":"can i use coinbase wallet","answer":"If it supports required chain and connection flow, yes.","tags":["wallet","support","investor"]}
{"question":"can i use hardware wallet like ledger","answer":"Yes, when connected through a supported wallet interface.","tags":["wallet","support","investor"]}
{"question":"can i use moonsale on my phone","answer":"Yes, MoonSale can be used on mobile with compatible wallet browser or WalletConnect flow.","tags":["wallet","support","investor"]}
{"question":"can I use moonsale tools for a token that already launched and is listed on DEX","answer":"Yes. Token Lock and Vesting at /lock and /vesting work for any ERC-20 including already-listed tokens. Useful for locking team allocation of an existing project.","tags":["token_lock","vesting","creator","dex","tools"]}
{"question":"can I use my token for both a presale and a separate token lock at the same time","answer":"Yes. Token Lock and presale are separate tools. You can lock team tokens via /lock while your presale is running. They operate independently.","tags":["token_lock","presale","creator"]}
{"question":"can I use quick presets for token supply","answer":"Yes, Moonsale has quick-fill buttons: 100M, 1B, 100B, and 1T. Click the one you want and it fills in the supply field. Saves time vs typing a big number.","tags":["token_creation","supply","creator"]}
{"question":"can i use token generator without launching presale","answer":"Yes. Token generator can be used independently. Launching a presale is optional.","tags":["token_create","tools","creator"]}
{"question":"can moonsale admin change my presale settings after I deploy","answer":"No. Core settings are on-chain and immutable — even Moonsale admin can't change them. What admin controls: KYC/audit badges, listing fee amounts, minimum lock enforcement, and platform fee %. They can't alter your price, softcap, hardcap, or vesting settings.","tags":["presale","admin","immutable","creator","trust"]}
{"question":"can moonsale team steal my funds","answer":"Sale and refund logic are contract-enforced on chain, not manual admin custody.","tags":["security","contracts","refund","investor"]}
{"question":"can one wallet create multiple presales","answer":"Yes, there's no limit on how many presales one wallet can create. Each one will need its own listing fee and token deposit.","tags":["presale","creator","wallet"]}
{"question":"Could not extract presale address from receipt","answer":"This usually means deploy receipt parsing failed. Verify both wallet confirmations were completed, wait for final confirmation on-chain, check explorer logs for presale creation event, refresh My Launches, and retry. If still failing, share tx hash, token address, and wallet with support.","tags":["presale","deploy","troubleshoot","receipt","creator"]}
{"question":"deposit your entire token pool upfront meaning","answer":"All launch tokens required for sale plus liquidity are deposited to contract before launch starts.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","deploy","tokenomics"]}
{"question":"description field max length in fair launch info","answer":"The description field in that form supports up to 1500 characters.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","listing","support"]}
{"question":"dev hasnt finalized its been 2 days since sale ended should i be worried","answer":"Finalization must happen for claim flow to open. If delayed, contact project/admin support and keep transaction records.","tags":["finalize","status","claim","support","investor"]}
{"question":"dev said whitelist open how do i join","answer":"Follow official project channels and never send funds to private wallets for whitelist access.","tags":["whitelist","security","support","investor"]}
{"question":"difference between kyc badge and audit badge","answer":"KYC verifies identity. Audit reviews smart-contract code and findings. They serve different trust purposes.","tags":["kyc","audit","badge","security"]}
{"question":"do fair launches get a security score too","answer":"Yes. Both presales and fair launches get the Security Score on their Security tab. The same 11 categories apply.","tags":["security_score","fair_launch","creator","investor"]}
{"question":"do i need bnb or eth to participte","answer":"Use native coin of the sale chain: BNB for BNB Chain sales and ETH for Ethereum sales.","tags":["bnb","ethereum","contribution","investor"]}
{"question":"do I need to bring my own token or can moonsale make one","answer":"Both work. You can paste any existing ERC-20 contract address into the create form, or use the Token Generator on Moonsale to deploy a fresh one. Tokens deployed through Moonsale's token factory are auto-verified on BscScan, which also helps your Security Score.","tags":["token","token_creation","creator","onboarding","security_score"]}
{"question":"do i need to do anythng or tokens come automaticly","answer":"You usually need to click Claim from the sale page. Tokens are not automatically sent in most sale flows.","tags":["claim","investor","presale","fair_launch"]}
{"question":"do I need to make an account before launching","answer":"No account needed. Just connect your wallet and you're good to go. Moonsale is fully permissionless — no signups, no approvals, no gatekeeping.","tags":["onboarding","creator","permissionless","wallet"]}
{"question":"do i need to make an account or just wallet","answer":"Wallet connection is usually enough for on-chain participation.","tags":["wallet","investor","how_it_works"]}
{"question":"do I need to pay a fee to use the vesting tool","answer":"Yes, there's a vesting setup fee (flat fee in BNB/ETH). Shown on the /vesting page before you create a schedule. Plus gas.","tags":["vesting","fees","creator"]}
{"question":"do testnet deploys cost real money","answer":"No. Testnet uses test tokens (tBNB or Sepolia ETH) which have no real value. Gas fees on testnet use test tokens. Listing fee on testnet is typically zero. Get test tokens from faucets.","tags":["testnet","fees","creator"]}
{"question":"does a fair launch automatically close when end time hits or does the creator need to do something","answer":"The sale stops accepting contributions at end time. But the creator still needs to manually finalize it from My Launches. It doesn't auto-finalize. Do it quickly after end time or investors get anxious.","tags":["fair_launch","finalization","creator","end_time"]}
{"question":"does a standard token mean I can't mint more later","answer":"Correct. A standard token has a fixed supply — whatever you set at creation is all there'll ever be. No minting after deploy. If you want to be able to mint later, choose the Mintable+Burnable type.","tags":["token_creation","standard_token","mintable","creator"]}
{"question":"does moonsale charge any ongoing fees for my token after creation","answer":"No ongoing fees from Moonsale for the token itself. The creation fee is one-time. If you have a Liquidity Generator token the fees go to your LP and marketing wallet — that's your own setup, not Moonsale taking a cut.","tags":["fees","token_creation","creator"]}
{"question":"does social presence really affect the security score","answer":"Yes but only 1 point max. You get it by having all 4 of: Twitter URL, Telegram URL, Website URL, and Logo URL filled in. Missing any one of them reduces the score (3 of 4 = 0.67pt, 2 of 4 = 0.33pt). Easy 1pt — just fill in your socials.","tags":["security_score","social_presence","creator","project_info"]}
{"question":"does the light/dark color scheme toggle affect anything functional","answer":"Just UI preference. Toggle between light and dark mode in the sidebar/footer. Doesn't affect any functionality or on-chain stuff.","tags":["ui","support"]}
{"question":"does the platform fee affect how much goes to liquidity","answer":"Yes, plan accordingly. If you raise 10 BNB, platform takes its %, remaining goes to liquidity % and your share. So if fee is 2% and liquidity is 60%: 0.2 BNB to platform, ~5.88 BNB to liquidity, ~3.92 BNB to you (rough math — check exact formula).","tags":["fees","liquidity","creator","platform_fee"]}
{"question":"does the security score care about vesting schedules or just locks","answer":"Security Score specifically looks at the Team Token Lock category — it checks MoonsaleTokenLock for locks by the creator. Vesting schedules through /vesting are separate and not directly counted in the Team Token Lock category in the same way.","tags":["security_score","token_lock","vesting","creator"]}
{"question":"does the security score update live or is it static","answer":"It updates live as on-chain data loads. Some checks like Contract Verified are cached 1 hour server-side. Team token lock is read client-side via wagmi hooks. Score recalculates as data comes in. Once a sale is deployed the score stabilizes quickly.","tags":["security_score","creator","support"]}
{"question":"explain fair launch like I'm 5","answer":"You put a fixed number of tokens into a pool. People send BNB/ETH in. At the end, all the BNB gets split proportionally — whoever put in 10% of the total BNB gets 10% of the tokens. Price isn't fixed, it depends on how much total is raised. More people = higher price per token.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","investor","onboarding"]}
{"question":"explain vesting with a real example","answer":"Say you create a vesting schedule: 1,000,000 tokens, TGE 20%, cliff 60 days, duration 365 days. On start date your beneficiary gets 200,000 tokens (20% TGE). Then nothing for 60 days (cliff). After cliff, the remaining 800,000 tokens unlock evenly every second over 365 days — about 2,191 tokens per day.","tags":["vesting","creator","example","tge","cliff"]}
{"question":"failed sale refund has deadline or can i claim anytime","answer":"MoonSale documentation states no refund deadline for failed or cancelled sales.","tags":["refund","softcap","investor","support"]}
{"question":"fair launch has no hardcap so it can go forever","answer":"No. Fair launch has defined start/end time even without hardcap.","tags":["fair_launch","hardcap","status","investor"]}
{"question":"fair launch has no hardcap so it can run forever","answer":"It runs until the end time you set. There's no hardcap to stop it early. You set start and end times just like a presale. After end time the creator finalizes and that locks the final price.","tags":["fair_launch","hardcap","creator","end_time"]}
{"question":"fair launch price keeps changing while sale is live, is that normal","answer":"Totally normal. The price estimate updates live as people contribute. More contributions = higher price. Investors see an estimate that changes, but the FINAL price is only locked when you finalize after sale ends. Tell your community this is expected behavior.","tags":["fair_launch","price","investor","creator","support"]}
{"question":"fair launch steps token config info deploy","answer":"Flow is Token selection, Config setup, Project Info, then Review and Deploy.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","how_it_works"]}
{"question":"fair launch vs presale which gets a better security score","answer":"Both can max the Security Score. The difference is: presale has a hardcap (reassures investors on max raise), fair launch has price discovery. Security Score categories like LP lock, team lock, KYC, audit, contract verified are the same for both.","tags":["fair_launch","presale","security_score","creator"]}
{"question":"finalization transaction failed with gas error, what do I do","answer":"Try again with higher gas. Finalization can be a heavier transaction since it's adding liquidity. If you're on BSC make sure your gas settings are appropriate. If it keeps failing, contact Moonsale support.","tags":["finalization","creator","support","gas","error"]}
{"question":"finalize button not showing for me","answer":"The Finalize button only shows for the wallet that deployed the presale. Make sure you're connected with the same wallet you used to create it. Also the sale needs to have ended and met softcap.","tags":["finalization","creator","support","wallet"]}
{"question":"gas fee too high any way to reduce","answer":"Wait for lower congestion or tune gas settings carefully. Very low gas can cause failure or long pending transactions.","tags":["wallet","support","contribution"]}
{"question":"hardcap reached in 2 min i didnt get in is there another chance","answer":"If hardcap is filled, further buys are blocked. Track upcoming launches for next opportunity.","tags":["hardcap","status","presale","investor"]}
{"question":"help my bnb is gone and no tokens","answer":"Verify tx hash and contribution record on sale page. Contributions do not instantly appear as tokens before finalization. If mismatch remains, contact admin with wallet and tx hash.","tags":["contribution","claim","support","investor"]}
{"question":"honeypot detection testnet not applicable meaning","answer":"That check is not available in current testnet context, so result is informational rather than pass or fail.","tags":["scanner","testnet","security","creator"]}
{"question":"how do i add buybot to my telegram group","answer":"Use official MoonSale BuyBot instructions and grant required Telegram bot permissions in your group.","tags":["buybot","telegram","support","tools"]}
{"question":"how do I add my logo to the presale page","answer":"In the project info section of the create form there's a Logo URL field. Host your logo image somewhere (IPFS, Imgur, your own server) and paste the direct image URL. It should be a square image for best results.","tags":["presale","logo","creator","project_info"]}
{"question":"how do i buy into dis presale","answer":"Open the sale page, connect wallet on the correct chain, enter an amount within min/max limits, then confirm transaction. Claim after successful finalization.","tags":["presale","contribution","investor","how_it_works"]}
{"question":"how do I calculate how many tokens to put in the pool for a fair launch","answer":"Think about what price range you want. If you put 1,000,000 tokens and expect to raise 10 BNB, final price = 10 BNB ÷ 1,000,000 = 0.00001 BNB per token. More tokens in pool = lower price. Fewer tokens = higher price. Size the pool based on your target raise and desired price.","tags":["fair_launch","token_pool","creator","price"]}
{"question":"how do I calculate presale allocation percentage for the security score","answer":"(presale tokens + liquidity tokens) ÷ total supply × 100. Example: 1B total supply, 400M for presale, 200M for liquidity = 60% → full 5pts. Under 35% gets 0pts.","tags":["security_score","presale_allocation","creator","liquidity"]}
{"question":"how do i check if lp is actually locked","answer":"Use official lock references from the sale and verify lock contract data on chain.","tags":["liquidity","lp","lock","security","investor"]}
{"question":"how do I get a perfect 50/50 security score","answer":"Lock LP 365+ days (8pts), lock team tokens 365+ days via Moonsale locker (8pts), use Moonsale token factory = auto-verified contract (8pts), allocate ≥55% supply to presale+liquidity (5pts), set liquidity ≥85% (5pts), get KYC verified (5pts), get audit done (5pts), fill all 4 socials (1pt), set softcap ≥50 BNB (1pt), token deposited on-chain (2pts — automatic), no blacklist function (2pts). All 11 = 50/50.","tags":["security_score","creator","kyc","audit","lp_lock","token_lock","perfect_score"]}
{"question":"how do i get refund if project fails","answer":"Open the failed or cancelled sale page and click Refund using the same wallet that contributed.","tags":["refund","investor","support","presale","fair_launch"]}
{"question":"how do i kno how many tokens ill get before buying","answer":"Use the contribution estimate on the sale page. In fixed-rate presales it is stable by rate; in fair launch it is an estimate that can change until finalization.","tags":["contribution","investor","presale","fair_launch","price_discovery"]}
{"question":"how do i kno if im whitelisted","answer":"Whitelist status is checked by contract when you contribute. Non-approved wallets are rejected in whitelist-only sales.","tags":["whitelist","investor","presale","fair_launch"]}
{"question":"how do I know the exact current fee amounts since fees can change","answer":"Check the /fees page and also look at each tool's page before confirming — amounts are shown before each transaction. Admin can update fees anytime so always check current amounts right before transacting.","tags":["fees","creator","support"]}
{"question":"how do i lock lp tokens that i already have","answer":"Open lock tool, choose LP token, set lock amount and duration, then confirm transaction.","tags":["lock","lp","tools","liquidity","creator"]}
{"question":"how do I lock my team tokens on moonsale","answer":"Go to moonsale.app/lock. Enter your token address, amount to lock, set an unlock date (or use presets: 90/180/365 days). Add an optional lock title. Review the summary box and click Lock Tokens. Confirm 2 txns (approve + lock).","tags":["token_lock","creator","step_by_step"]}
{"question":"how do i pay listing fee where exactly on site","answer":"After deployment, use listing-fee step in your launch flow or My Launches panel.","tags":["listing_fee","creator","presale","fair_launch","how_it_works"]}
{"question":"how do I start launching on moonsale","answer":"First make sure you have a Web3 wallet (MetaMask or WalletConnect), some BNB or ETH for gas, and your token contract ready. If you don't have a token yet, use the Token Generator at moonsale.app/create-token. Then go create a presale or fair launch from the sidebar.","tags":["onboarding","creator","presale","wallet","launch"]}
{"question":"how do I test before going mainnet","answer":"Switch your wallet to BNB Testnet or Sepolia and do everything there first. The listing fee on testnet is usually zero so you can test the full flow for free. Always test before spending on mainnet.","tags":["testnet","testing","creator","onboarding"]}
{"question":"how do I withdraw my unsold or refunded tokens after a failed presale","answer":"After presale fails or is cancelled, go to My Launches, find the sale, click Withdraw Tokens. Confirm the txn and tokens come back to your wallet.","tags":["withdraw","presale","creator","cancel","failed","refund"]}
{"question":"how do investors verify my team token lock is real","answer":"Each lock has a unique detail page at moonsale.app/token-lock/[lockId]. Share that URL in your Telegram/Discord. Anyone can view the locked amount, unlock date, and token address. Also shows in the Security tab of your presale page as a 'View Lock' link.","tags":["token_lock","investor","trust","verification"]}
{"question":"how does moonsale check if a contract is verified","answer":"Server-side via the Etherscan V2 unified API. The platform fetches your token's source code from BscScan/Etherscan. Result is cached for 1 hour. If verified = 8pts. Not verified = 0pts + critical risk.","tags":["security_score","contract_verified","creator","bscscan","etherscan"]}
{"question":"how does the charity campaign on moonsale work","answer":"That links to fundbeep.com which is a separate platform for charity campaigns. It's listed under Moonsale's navigation as a 'Give Back' option but is its own product.","tags":["charity","tools"]}
{"question":"how does the token deposited check work in the security score","answer":"The platform reads the presale contract's token balance directly on-chain. If the balance covers what the sale needs, the check passes automatically (2pts). This happens when you create your presale and deposit tokens — no extra step needed. It auto-passes.","tags":["security_score","token_deposit","creator"]}
{"question":"how does the tokenomics creator work step by step","answer":"1) Enter your token/project name. 2) Fill in allocation rows (color, category name, % of supply, lockup description). 3) Watch the live donut chart update. 4) Make sure all % sum to 100%. 5) Click Generate PDF — downloads a formatted report with table + donut chart.","tags":["tokenomics_creator","creator","step_by_step","tools"]}
{"question":"how is dis diffrent from pinksale","answer":"Use official docs to compare launch flow, fees, refund behavior, and lock rules. I can provide verified MoonSale details for side-by-side checks.","tags":["comparison","general","investor"]}
{"question":"how is the security score calculated","answer":"11 categories each scored 0–3, multiplied by their weight, summed to max 50. Critical categories (Liquidity Lock, Team Token Lock, Contract Verified) each worth 8pts. High categories (Presale Allocation, Liquidity %, KYC, Audit) worth 5pts each. Standard (Token Deposited, No Blacklist) worth 2pts each. Low (Social Presence, Softcap Size) worth 1pt each.","tags":["security_score","creator","investor"]}
{"question":"how is total deposit calculated in review","answer":"Total Deposit equals Tokens for Sale plus Tokens for Liquidity.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","tokenomics","deploy"]}
{"question":"how long does it take to launch a presale start to finish","answer":"If you have everything ready, maybe 15–20 minutes. Deploy token (if needed) → create presale (2 txns) → pay listing fee (1 txn) → you're live. The forms are straightforward.","tags":["onboarding","creator","presale","timeline"]}
{"question":"How many confirmations are required when deploying a presale","answer":"Two confirmations are required. First you approve token transfer. Second the factory deploys the presale and pulls the required token amount.","tags":["presale","deploy","creator","atomic"]}
{"question":"how many tokens do I need to deposit for the presale","answer":"The contract calculates this based on your price and hardcap plus what goes to liquidity. Basically: (hardcap ÷ token price) + (hardcap × liquidity% ÷ token price at listing rate). The form should show you the required amount. Always have enough tokens in your wallet before deploying.","tags":["presale","token_deposit","creator","liquidity"]}
{"question":"how many tokens should I lock as team allocation","answer":"No hard rule, but for full Security Score points (8pts) you need team tokens locked for 365+ days. Lock whatever your team allocation is. Showing 0% team tokens (no locks needed because you have no team allocation) is N/A and harmlessly excluded from the score.","tags":["token_lock","security_score","creator","team_allocation"]}
{"question":"how much does token creation cost on moonsale","answer":"There's a flat fee in BNB (on BSC) or ETH (on Ethereum) shown on the token generator page before you deploy, plus gas fees on top. Exact amount varies — check the page for current rates.","tags":["fees","token_creation","creator"]}
{"question":"how much is the listing fee","answer":"It varies by chain and is set by the platform admin. The exact amount in BNB or ETH is shown in the create form before you deploy AND again on the My Launches page when you go to pay. Check the /fees page too.","tags":["listing_fee","fees","creator","presale"]}
{"question":"how often can i claim during vesting period like daily or only once","answer":"Claim cadence depends on vesting schedule. Some are continuous-linear, others interval-based.","tags":["vesting","claim","investor"]}
{"question":"how to fix pair has existing liquidity block","answer":"Remove existing pair liquidity first, then re-run eligibility scan, or launch with a token that has no existing liquid pair.","tags":["fair_launch","liquidity","dex","scanner","creator"]}
{"question":"I accidentally finalized too early before everyone contributed","answer":"Once finalized it's done — that's a blockchain transaction and it's permanent. Finalization is a manual step for exactly this reason — to make sure the creator is ready. Be careful and only finalize when you're genuinely done with the sale.","tags":["finalization","creator","support","immutable"]}
{"question":"I accidentally sent tokens to the lock contract directly, are they lost","answer":"Tokens sent directly to the contract address outside the normal lock flow might be unrecoverable. Always use the Moonsale UI at /lock to create locks properly. Never send tokens to contract addresses manually.","tags":["token_lock","support","creator","error"]}
{"question":"i approved but 2nd txn failed now what","answer":"Approval can succeed while buy fails due to gas, limits, or wrong chain. Recheck settings and retry.","tags":["metamask","wallet","support","contribution"]}
{"question":"I can't find my presale in My Launches","answer":"Make sure you're connected with the EXACT same wallet you used to deploy. Moonsale shows your launches based on the connected wallet. Wrong wallet = empty My Launches.","tags":["presale","creator","support","wallet","ui"]}
{"question":"i cant read all this just tell me buy or no buy","answer":"I cannot provide financial advice. I can help you quickly evaluate risk signals so you can decide.","tags":["risk","security","investor","general"]}
{"question":"i changed wallet mid presale will my old contribution be lost","answer":"Contribution remains tied to original wallet. Claim and refund must be done from that wallet.","tags":["wallet","claim","refund","investor"]}
{"question":"i claimed but tokens not in my wallet","answer":"Verify claim tx success, correct chain, and token contract import in your wallet. Also make sure you are using the same contribution wallet.","tags":["claim","wallet","metamask","support"]}
{"question":"i conected my wallet but cant see the buy buton","answer":"If Buy is missing, check correct network, Live status, whitelist requirement, and wallet eligibility. Refresh and reconnect wallet if needed.","tags":["wallet","support","presale","contribution"]}
{"question":"I created a token on ETH, can I run the presale on BNB","answer":"No. The token and presale must be on the same chain. If your token is on ETH, your presale runs on ETH with ETH contributions. A BNB presale needs a BNB chain token.","tags":["chains","bnb","ethereum","presale","token","support"]}
{"question":"I deployed a presale but forgot to enable vesting, can I add it now","answer":"No. Vesting settings are set during deployment and can't be changed after. If you need vesting and forgot to enable it, your options are: 1) cancel and redeploy with vesting enabled, or 2) set up separate vesting schedules manually via /vesting for individual beneficiaries after the sale.","tags":["vesting","presale","creator","support","cancel"]}
{"question":"I deployed a presale but my wallet disconnected midway, did my presale get created","answer":"If BOTH transactions confirmed on-chain, yes your presale exists regardless of wallet disconnection. Check your transaction history on the block explorer for your wallet address. If the second txn failed you'll need to redeploy.","tags":["presale","creator","support","wallet","transactions"]}
{"question":"i dont hav metamask can i use trust wallet","answer":"Yes. Trust Wallet and other compatible wallets can work if they support required chain and dApp connection.","tags":["wallet","walletconnect","support","investor"]}
{"question":"I finalized but the token price on PancakeSwap is way different from presale price, is that normal","answer":"The listing price depends on how liquidity was added. The ratio of BNB (liquidity %) to tokens (at presale rate) determines the initial DEX price. It should match presale price if you used 100% of expected amounts. If not, check your liquidity % settings and token amounts.","tags":["finalization","dex","price","pancakeswap","creator","support"]}
{"question":"i got 20 percent on tge wen do i get the rest","answer":"Remaining tokens unlock according to cliff and vesting duration configured for that sale.","tags":["tge","vesting","claim","investor"]}
{"question":"i got partial refund where did rest go","answer":"Partial return can happen with early-withdraw penalties or mixed transaction states. Verify each tx on explorer.","tags":["refund","withdraw","penalty","investor","support"]}
{"question":"i got whitelisted but sale starts wen","answer":"Check the sale countdown for exact start time and timezone.","tags":["whitelist","status","investor"]}
{"question":"I have 5 team members each needing separate vesting, do I create 5 separate schedules","answer":"Yes. Create one vesting schedule per beneficiary wallet. Each gets its own detail page and dashboard card. They each claim independently.","tags":["vesting","creator","team_allocation","beneficiary"]}
{"question":"I have no team allocation, does the team token lock category hurt my score","answer":"Nope. If you have no team locks at all (because you have no team allocation), that category shows as N/A and is excluded from your total. It doesn't count as 0 — it's just skipped. Your max possible score adjusts accordingly.","tags":["security_score","token_lock","creator","na"]}
{"question":"I have unsold tokens after the presale, what happens to them","answer":"Do not send unsold tokens anywhere before finalizing. The contract needs its full token balance to add liquidity properly. After finalization, unsold tokens (beyond what went to presale buyers and liquidity) are typically returned or burned depending on settings. Never manually transfer tokens out before finalization.","tags":["presale","unsold_tokens","finalization","creator","support"]}
{"question":"I locked tokens but set the wrong amount, can I unlock early to fix it","answer":"No. Locks are locked until the unlock date. You can't unlock early or change the amount. Make sure you enter the right amount before confirming. That's why the 'What will happen' green summary box is there — read it carefully before confirming.","tags":["token_lock","creator","support","immutable"]}
{"question":"I made a mistake in my token supply after deploying, can I fix it","answer":"No. Once deployed the supply is set on-chain and can't be changed (unless you chose mintable+burnable type, then you can mint more but can't reduce supply). If you made a big mistake you'll need to redeploy a new token, which means paying the creation fee again.","tags":["token_creation","support","creator","immutable"]}
{"question":"I maximized all 11 security score categories, what does my score page look like","answer":"Big '50 / 50' with a circular progress ring showing 100%. All 11 rows show green checkmark '3/3 No Risk'. No critical risks banner. It's the ideal state — very few projects achieve this.","tags":["security_score","creator","perfect_score"]}
{"question":"I paid the listing fee but my presale still isn't showing publicly","answer":"First check: did the fee txn actually confirm? Look in your wallet transaction history. If confirmed, try refreshing My Launches. If status still shows Pending after confirmed fee payment, contact Moonsale support — it might be a display issue.","tags":["listing_fee","presale","support","visibility","creator"]}
{"question":"i sent bnb but tokens didnt come yet","answer":"Contributed funds are recorded first. Tokens become claimable only after successful finalization and according to vesting terms.","tags":["contribution","claim","investor","vesting"]}
{"question":"I set the wrong start time and already deployed, can I fix it","answer":"Unfortunately no. Start and end times are locked after deployment. If the error is major enough, your only option is to cancel the presale (if it hasn't started), withdraw your tokens, and redeploy with correct settings.","tags":["presale","creator","support","immutable","cancel"]}
{"question":"I set the wrong token pool size for a fair launch I already deployed, can I fix it","answer":"No. Token pool size is locked on deployment. If it's a significant mistake, cancel the fair launch (before investors contribute if possible), withdraw your tokens, and redeploy with the correct pool size.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","support","cancel","immutable"]}
{"question":"i used wrong wallet address can i fix it","answer":"On-chain contribution ownership cannot be reassigned by support. Actions must come from original wallet.","tags":["wallet","security","support","investor"]}
{"question":"I want to cancel my presale that I haven't paid the listing fee for yet","answer":"Go to My Launches, find your pending sale, click Cancel, confirm txn. Then click Withdraw Tokens to get your deposited tokens back. This is the cleanest cancel scenario since no investors are involved.","tags":["cancel","presale","creator","listing_fee","withdraw"]}
{"question":"I want to do a second presale round after the first one succeeds, is that possible","answer":"Yes. After your first presale finalizes and the token is listed, you can create a new presale for any remaining token allocation. But note: investors may be wary of a second presale after listing since they can now buy on DEX. Plan this carefully.","tags":["presale","creator","second_round","dex"]}
{"question":"I want to set up multiple vesting schedules for many investors not just team","answer":"For presale investors vesting is set globally in the presale settings and applies to all investors. For individual custom schedules (advisors, partners, VCs) you create separate schedules at /vesting per beneficiary wallet.","tags":["vesting","creator","investor","presale","beneficiary"]}
{"question":"I want whitelist for an early round then open to public, can I do that","answer":"Yes. Enable whitelist at deployment, run the whitelisted phase, then remove the whitelist (or add everyone) to open it publicly before the sale ends. You manage the whitelist from your sale page.","tags":["whitelist","presale","creator","phases"]}
{"question":"I'm an anon dev, can I still launch","answer":"Yes. Moonsale is permissionless so anon devs can launch. But heads up — not having KYC will hurt your Security Score and investors will be more skeptical. You can still launch, just expect lower trust from the community.","tags":["kyc","security_score","creator","permissionless","anon"]}
{"question":"if I cancel how long before I can withdraw my tokens","answer":"Immediately after the cancel txn is confirmed. The Withdraw Tokens button appears right after cancellation.","tags":["cancel","withdraw","creator","presale"]}
{"question":"if i change token after filling info will values reset","answer":"Changing token can alter dependent values. Re-check config, info, and deposit calculations before deploying.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","token","support"]}
{"question":"if i click start over does fair launch draft get erased","answer":"Start over resets builder flow. If draft persistence exists, always re-check every field before deploy.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","support"]}
{"question":"if i contributed in 3 separate transactions do i refund all at once","answer":"Refund is contract-calculated for your eligible contribution balance from that wallet.","tags":["refund","contribution","investor","contracts"]}
{"question":"if i lose access to my wallet do i lose vested tokens forever","answer":"Yes. On-chain claims require the original wallet access. Keep seed phrase and keys secure.","tags":["wallet","vesting","security","investor"]}
{"question":"if i remove existing pair liquidity can i retry fair launch","answer":"Yes, after resolving existing-liquidity condition, re-run scan and proceed if all blocking checks pass.","tags":["fair_launch","liquidity","scanner","creator"]}
{"question":"if I use the moonsale token generator does my contract get verified on BscScan automatically","answer":"Yes! Tokens deployed through the Moonsale token factory are auto-verified on BscScan/Etherscan. This also gives you full 8 points in the Contract Verified category of the Security Score.","tags":["token_creation","contract_verified","security_score","bscscan","creator"]}
{"question":"if i withdraw early do i lose all my bnb or just some","answer":"Early withdrawal usually applies a penalty, not total loss. Exact amount depends on sale rules.","tags":["withdraw","penalty","refund","investor"]}
{"question":"if more ppl join does my token amount go down","answer":"In fair launch your share is proportional. If total raised grows and you do not add more, your percentage share decreases.","tags":["fair_launch","price_discovery","investor"]}
{"question":"if my presale fails do I get the platform fee back","answer":"Platform fee is only charged at finalization, which only happens if the sale succeeds. If the presale fails, no finalization happens so no platform fee is charged. You just lose the listing fee.","tags":["fees","presale","failed","refund","platform_fee"]}
{"question":"if my score is low can I improve it after launch","answer":"Some things can be improved post-deploy: get KYC verified, submit audit, add team token locks (improves team lock category), fill in all socials if you missed them. LP lock is set at finalization so that's locked in. Plan to maximize score BEFORE going live.","tags":["security_score","creator","kyc","audit","token_lock"]}
{"question":"if presale fails do i get listing fee back","answer":"Listing-fee refund depends on current platform policy. Check official docs for latest terms.","tags":["fees","listing_fee","creator","support"]}
{"question":"if softcap is not met in fair launch what happens","answer":"Sale is unsuccessful and contributors use refund flow according to contract rules.","tags":["fair_launch","softcap","refund","investor"]}
{"question":"if you do not know the answer what should happen","answer":"If no verified answer is available, ask user to wait for admin support reply and share official docs links as temporary guidance.","tags":["support","general"]}
{"question":"im not on whitelist can i still buy","answer":"Only if sale is public. In whitelist-only mode, non-whitelisted wallets cannot buy.","tags":["whitelist","investor","presale","fair_launch"]}
{"question":"is 2 percent platform fee charged if fair launch fails","answer":"The label says fee is on successful raise, so failed outcome does not trigger that success-based fee.","tags":["fees","fair_launch","creator","softcap"]}
{"question":"is logo url optional in project info","answer":"Yes, logo URL is optional but recommended for trust and presentation.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","listing","marketing"]}
{"question":"is marketing support available through moonsale","answer":"Yes via icogemhunters.com/moonsale-services — that's the parent ecosystem's marketing services. Moonsale itself is the launchpad tool; ICO Gem Hunters handles marketing.","tags":["marketing","creator","tools"]}
{"question":"is moonsale an exchange or what exactly","answer":"MoonSale is a launchpad for presales and fair launches, plus tools like lock, vesting, scanner, and token generator.","tags":["general","how_it_works","presale","fair_launch"]}
{"question":"is moonsale permissionless or do they approve my project first","answer":"Fully permissionless. You deploy your presale yourself, pay the listing fee, and it goes live — no one from Moonsale needs to approve it. KYC and Audit badges are optional things you can apply for to build trust, but they're not required to launch.","tags":["permissionless","creator","kyc","audit","onboarding"]}
{"question":"is moonsale safe or can devs rug anytime","answer":"MoonSale has audited contracts and investor safeguards, but project risk remains. Always do your own research before investing.","tags":["security","safe","risk","investor"]}
{"question":"is refund automatic or do i have to click something","answer":"You usually need to click Refund. Eligibility is on-chain, but claiming refund still requires wallet transaction.","tags":["refund","investor","how_it_works"]}
{"question":"is the listing fee refundable if I cancel my presale","answer":"No. Once you pay the listing fee it's paid. If you cancel your presale you get your deposited tokens back but not the listing fee.","tags":["listing_fee","fees","cancel","creator","refund"]}
{"question":"is the listing fee the same for presale and fair launch","answer":"May differ. Both are set by the platform admin and can be different. Check the /fees page for current rates or look at the create form before deploying.","tags":["listing_fee","fees","presale","fair_launch","creator"]}
{"question":"is the platform fee taken from my raised funds or from investors","answer":"From your raised funds at finalization. It's a percentage of total BNB/ETH raised. So if you raise 10 BNB and platform fee is 2%, you get 9.8 BNB to work with (minus whatever goes to liquidity).","tags":["fees","creator","finalization","platform_fee"]}
{"question":"is the token lock fee flat or a percentage of the locked amount","answer":"Flat fee per lock, regardless of amount locked. Shown on /lock page before you confirm.","tags":["token_lock","fees","creator"]}
{"question":"is the tokenomics creator free to use","answer":"Yes, the Tokenomics Creator at /tokenomics-creator is free. No fee to generate the PDF. It's an AI-powered tool to help you visualize and export your token allocation.","tags":["tokenomics_creator","creator","free","tools"]}
{"question":"is the vesting setup fee per schedule or one flat fee total","answer":"Per schedule. Each vesting schedule creation costs the fee. If you create 5 schedules for 5 team members, you pay the fee 5 times.","tags":["vesting","fees","creator"]}
{"question":"is there a deadline to finalize after the sale ends","answer":"Yes there's a finalization window. If you don't finalize in time, investors can mark the sale as failed and claim refunds. Don't wait — finalize immediately after your sale ends and softcap is met.","tags":["finalization","creator","deadline","refund"]}
{"question":"is there a minimum or maximum raise amount","answer":"You set your own softcap and hardcap, so technically you decide the range. The platform doesn't enforce a global minimum raise amount. But the Security Score rewards a softcap of 50+ BNB for the full point in that category.","tags":["softcap","hardcap","presale","creator","security_score"]}
{"question":"is there a way to preview my token before actually deploying","answer":"No preview/simulation feature on the UI, but you can always deploy to testnet first (BNB Testnet or Sepolia) to check everything looks right before mainnet. Testnet deploys are cheap.","tags":["token_creation","testnet","creator","support"]}
{"question":"is there an API to integrate moonsale data into my own site","answer":"Not publicly documented. Moonsale is primarily a UI-based platform. For on-chain data integration, you can read the smart contracts directly using their ABIs on BscScan/Etherscan.","tags":["api","developer","integration"]}
{"question":"is there any way to extend my presale end time","answer":"No. End time is locked on-chain after deployment. You can't extend it. If the sale hasn't hit softcap by end time it fails automatically. Plan your end time carefully — give enough time but not too long.","tags":["presale","end_time","creator","immutable","support"]}
{"question":"is there slippage in fair launch like on dex","answer":"Fair launch uses sale allocation math, not regular DEX swap slippage during contribution.","tags":["fair_launch","price_discovery","investor"]}
{"question":"is this legit or another rug","answer":"MoonSale has contract-level protections like refund and lock logic, but project-level risk still exists. Always review team credibility, token distribution, lock terms, and community quality before investing.","tags":["security","risk","investor","liquidity"]}
{"question":"is whitepaper url optional in fair launch info","answer":"Yes, whitepaper URL is optional in that project info form.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","listing","whitepaper"]}
{"question":"its past start time but i cant buy yet why","answer":"Check whitelist mode, chain mismatch, and whether publish/final setup steps are completed.","tags":["status","whitelist","wallet","investor"]}
{"question":"kyc badge means dev is doxxed","answer":"KYC badge indicates identity verification was completed under platform process. It does not remove all risk.","tags":["kyc","badge","security","investor"]}
{"question":"KYC gives 5 points, how long does KYC take","answer":"Apply through moonsale.app/kyc-audit. The admin manually reviews your documents and enables the badge. Timing varies — can be a few hours to a day depending on workload. Apply before your launch date.","tags":["kyc","security_score","creator"]}
{"question":"liquidity 65 percent locked 90d meaning","answer":"65% of raised funds is used for liquidity and LP lock duration is set to 90 days.","tags":["fair_launch","liquidity","lock","creator","investor"]}
{"question":"liquidity percentage category — 85% is max points but minimum required is 51%","answer":"Correct. The platform requires minimum 51% to even deploy. But for max Security Score points (5/5) you need ≥85%. Between 51–64% you get 1/3 of points (1.67pts). 65–84% gives 2/3 (3.33pts). 85%+ gives full 5pts.","tags":["security_score","liquidity","creator"]}
{"question":"listing fee is per chain or same everywhere","answer":"Fee policy can vary by chain/product. Verify exact current values on official fees page.","tags":["fees","listing_fee","chains","creator"]}
{"question":"market sets token price in fair launch meaning","answer":"Final token price is discovered from total raised amount and total token pool at finalization.","tags":["fair_launch","price_discovery","tokenomics","investor"]}
{"question":"metamask keeps rejecting the txn idk why","answer":"Check chain, gas balance, pending queue, and contribution limits. Retry after fixing those conditions.","tags":["metamask","wallet","support","contribution"]}
{"question":"min buy 0.01 bnb meaning","answer":"Each contribution must be at least 0.01 BNB in that configuration.","tags":["fair_launch","contribution","creator","investor"]}
{"question":"mintable token means I can print more tokens whenever I want","answer":"If you chose Mintable+Burnable type, yes the owner wallet can mint additional tokens. This is a red flag to many investors since it can be used to dilute supply. Be transparent about your minting policy if you go this route.","tags":["mintable","token_creation","creator","investor","trust"]}
{"question":"moonsale said my token has a blacklist function but it doesn't, why","answer":"The scanner might be detecting a function name or signature that matches blacklist patterns. Review your token contract code for any function names containing 'blacklist', 'ban', 'block' etc. Even innocuous functions with those names can trigger the check. If it's a false positive, document it clearly for your community.","tags":["blacklist","scanner","creator","support","security_score"]}
{"question":"my cliff is done but vesting dashboard shows 0 claimable, why","answer":"Double-check the dates. Maybe the cliff hasn't actually ended yet (check exact timestamps not just day count). Also check if you're logged in with the beneficiary wallet, not the creator wallet. The claim button only works for the beneficiary.","tags":["vesting","support","investor","beneficiary","cliff"]}
{"question":"my estimated tokens keep changing on fair launch is that a bug","answer":"Usually not a bug. Fair launch estimates update with changing total raised before finalization.","tags":["fair_launch","price_discovery","investor","support"]}
{"question":"my external token isn't verified, will I fail the contract verified check","answer":"Yes. Contract Verified checks the token on BscScan/Etherscan. If source code isn't public there, you get 0 on that category (8pts lost + critical risk banner). Verify your contract on the block explorer before launching if you're using an external token.","tags":["security_score","contract_verified","critical_risk","creator","bscscan"]}
{"question":"my presale ended but the status still says live on the page","answer":"The page polls the blockchain every few seconds. Give it a moment. If status doesn't update try a hard refresh. If it persists it might be a display glitch — the underlying on-chain state is what matters, check your sale contract on the block explorer.","tags":["presale","support","status","ui"]}
{"question":"my presale hit softcap and ended, what do I do now","answer":"Go to My Launches, find your presale, click Finalize in the owner panel. Confirm the txn. This adds liquidity to DEX, locks the LP, and makes tokens claimable for investors. Do this ASAP — delays make investors nervous.","tags":["finalization","presale","creator","step_by_step"]}
{"question":"my presale page looks empty or blank to investors, why","answer":"Probably didn't fill in the project info section — description, logo, socials. These fields are technically optional during deploy but make your page look legit. Also affects Security Score (Social Presence category). Check if your sale page has all details.","tags":["presale","project_info","creator","support","security_score"]}
{"question":"my presale page shows nothing or is completely blank","answer":"Common causes: (1) Not paid listing fee yet — presale in Pending state. (2) Project info section not filled in at deploy time. (3) Wrong chain selected in your wallet. (4) Browser cache issue — try hard refresh or different browser.","tags":["presale","support","visibility","listing_fee","creator"]}
{"question":"my token has a blacklist function, will that be a problem","answer":"Yes it will. The Security Score scanner checks for blacklist functions in your token bytecode. If detected, your No Blacklist Function category scores 0 (Risky) and you lose 2 pts. More importantly it looks suspicious to investors. Avoid blacklist functions if possible.","tags":["blacklist","security_score","token","creator","scanner"]}
{"question":"my token has an owner function to pause transfers, does that count as a blacklist function","answer":"The scanner checks for blacklist-style functions specifically. A general pause function might or might not trigger it depending on implementation. If you're worried, test your token through the Token Scanner at /token-scanner to check before launch.","tags":["blacklist","security_score","scanner","creator","token"]}
{"question":"no kyc on this project shud i still invest","answer":"No KYC means higher uncertainty. Review risk factors carefully and only invest what you can afford to lose.","tags":["kyc","risk","security","investor"]}
{"question":"no vesting in deploy review meaning","answer":"No vesting means contributors receive fully claimable allocation at claim-open, not gradual unlock.","tags":["fair_launch","claim","vesting","investor"]}
{"question":"ok so i connect wallet then what","answer":"Open a Live sale, review limits and tokenomics, enter amount, confirm tx, and claim after finalization.","tags":["investor","wallet","presale","fair_launch","how_it_works"]}
{"question":"pair exists but empty vs pair has existing liquidity difference","answer":"Pair exists but empty has zero reserves and may be acceptable; pair has existing liquidity means non-zero reserves and can trigger block.","tags":["liquidity","dex","scanner","fair_launch","creator"]}
{"question":"pair has existing liquidity why dangerous","answer":"Existing holders can arbitrage or drain value from a newly added pool if the launch starts with an already-liquid pair.","tags":["liquidity","security","dex","fair_launch"]}
{"question":"platform fee 2 percent of successful raise when charged","answer":"This fee is applied only on successful raise outcome, typically at finalization stage.","tags":["fees","fair_launch","creator","finalize"]}
{"question":"platform takes percent of raised funds how much exactly","answer":"MoonSale has documented platform fee model. Check official fees page for latest exact values.","tags":["fees","listing_fee","revenue","creator"]}
{"question":"platform unlocked token limit 20 percent meaning","answer":"Creator cannot leave more than 20% of total supply unlocked after deployment.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","security","tokenomics"]}
{"question":"price at softcap shows 0.00000000 bnb per token why","answer":"That usually means displayed precision is rounding a very small number. The underlying fair-launch math still applies.","tags":["fair_launch","price_discovery","tokenomics","support"]}
{"question":"price keeps changing on fair launch is that normal","answer":"Yes. Fair launch estimates can change until finalization as total raised changes.","tags":["fair_launch","price_discovery","investor"]}
{"question":"project finalized but i still cant claim","answer":"Refresh page, reconnect same wallet, confirm correct network, and check vesting/cliff settings. If still blocked, contact admin with sale link and wallet address.","tags":["claim","finalize","vesting","support"]}
{"question":"project name from token can i edit","answer":"Project name is auto-filled from token metadata in this flow. If token metadata is wrong, update token source details or change token.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","token","support"]}
{"question":"proxy detection original contract meaning","answer":"Original contract means proxy behavior was not detected in that scan result.","tags":["scanner","security","token","creator"]}
{"question":"sale ended 2 hrs ago still no claim button","answer":"Claim appears only after finalize action is completed. If not finalized yet, claim stays unavailable.","tags":["claim","finalize","status","investor"]}
{"question":"sale failed but refund button not showing","answer":"Use exact contribution wallet on correct chain. If still hidden, send sale link and wallet to admin support.","tags":["refund","support","wallet","investor"]}
{"question":"sale finalized but claim button still not showing its been 3 hours","answer":"Recheck wallet and chain, refresh page, then verify vesting conditions. If still missing, contact admin with sale link and wallet.","tags":["claim","finalize","support","wallet"]}
{"question":"sale got cancled by dev will i get full refund","answer":"If sale is cancelled and refund is enabled by contract conditions, contributors can refund from the sale page.","tags":["cancel","refund","investor","presale","fair_launch"]}
{"question":"sale supposed to end today but still showing live","answer":"Confirm timezone/block-time interpretation. UI cache can temporarily lag status updates.","tags":["status","support","investor","presale","fair_launch"]}
{"question":"scanner passed ownership but still blocked why","answer":"Any single blocking condition can fail deployment even if other checks pass.","tags":["scanner","fair_launch","security","creator"]}
{"question":"score shows red critical risks banner but total score is 40/50, will investors avoid me","answer":"Yes likely. The red banner overrides the total. Even 40/50 with a critical risk is a red flag. Investors are told to never ignore critical risks. Fix the critical categories — especially LP lock and team token lock.","tags":["security_score","critical_risk","investor","creator","lp_lock","token_lock"]}
{"question":"security score shows N/A for some categories, is that bad","answer":"N/A means that category is either still loading on-chain data or genuinely not applicable (like team token lock when you have no team locks). N/A categories are excluded from the denominator so they don't penalize your score. Wait for data to load and N/A from loading will resolve.","tags":["security_score","na","creator","support"]}
{"question":"should i convert local time to utc before setting fair launch","answer":"Yes. The launch form uses UTC, so convert local timezone carefully to avoid wrong start or end window.","tags":["fair_launch","status","creator","support"]}
{"question":"softcap 0.01 bnb meaning in fair launch","answer":"Softcap is the minimum raise threshold required for a successful finalization.","tags":["fair_launch","softcap","creator","investor"]}
{"question":"softcap not reached wen do i get my money back","answer":"If softcap is not reached, sale fails and refund is available via smart contract on the sale page.","tags":["softcap","refund","investor","presale","fair_launch"]}
{"question":"someone in tg said moonsale is hacked is that true","answer":"Ignore unverified rumors. Trust only official MoonSale announcements and status updates.","tags":["security","support","general"]}
{"question":"someone is impersonating my project on moonsale, what do I do","answer":"Contact Moonsale support/admin immediately. In your real presale, prominently display your contract address and official links. Get a KYC badge to add credibility. Warn your community about the fake.","tags":["support","creator","kyc","security","impersonation"]}
{"question":"start utc and end utc in deploy review meaning","answer":"These are sale open and close times in UTC timezone.","tags":["fair_launch","status","creator","investor"]}
{"question":"sufficient token balance check meaning in deploy review","answer":"It confirms your wallet has at least the exact required token amount for contract deposit.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","deploy","token"]}
{"question":"team token lock calculation — what does weighted average mean","answer":"If you have multiple locks, Moonsale calculates: sum of (each lock amount × days remaining) divided by total locked amount. So a bigger lock with longer duration weighs more. Formula: Σ(amount × days) ÷ Σ(amount). Average needs to be ≥365 days for full 8pts.","tags":["security_score","token_lock","creator","weighted_average"]}
{"question":"team tokens locked or not how do i verify","answer":"Check team allocation lock or vesting contract addresses provided by project and verify on explorer.","tags":["lock","vesting","security","investor"]}
{"question":"testnet not applicable checks should i worry","answer":"Not-applicable checks are expected on some testnets; still ensure all mandatory blocking checks pass.","tags":["testnet","scanner","fair_launch","security"]}
{"question":"the first transaction went through but the second one failed, what now","answer":"The presale wasn't created. The first txn just approved the contract to spend tokens but didn't actually deploy anything. You can try deploying again — the approval might still be valid so you might only need to confirm the second txn. If not, repeat both.","tags":["presale","creator","support","transactions","deploy"]}
{"question":"the ICO calendar link goes to icogemhunters.com, is that related to moonsale","answer":"ICO Gem Hunters is the parent ecosystem. Moonsale projects should be discoverable there. It's a separate site from the launchpad itself.","tags":["ico_calendar","marketing","ecosystem"]}
{"question":"the tokenomics creator percentages don't add up to 100 and I can't export","answer":"All percentages MUST total exactly 100% before the Generate PDF button works. Add up your rows and adjust. Check for rounding errors.","tags":["tokenomics_creator","creator","support","tools"]}
{"question":"token management page shows nothing why","answer":"Connect the wallet with ownership/permissions and ensure correct chain selection.","tags":["token_management","wallet","support","creator"]}
{"question":"token scanner says honeypot but others say its fine which to trust","answer":"Treat scanner warnings seriously and cross-check owner permissions, transfer behavior, and other independent audits/tools.","tags":["scanner","security","risk","investor"]}
{"question":"tokenomics creator is free or paid","answer":"Check current pricing on the official tokenomics creator page because tool pricing may change.","tags":["tokenomics","tools","fees","support"]}
{"question":"tokens for sale vs tokens for liquidity difference in fair launch","answer":"Tokens for Sale are allocated to contributors; Tokens for Liquidity are reserved for DEX pool creation at finalization.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","liquidity","tokenomics"]}
{"question":"tokens to deposit value in review meaning","answer":"It is the exact token amount your wallet must approve and transfer to deploy the fair launch contract.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","deploy","token"]}
{"question":"transaction keeps failing at finalization with no clear error","answer":"Try: (1) Increase gas limit. (2) Check you have enough BNB/ETH for gas. (3) Make sure the presale contract still has the right token balance. (4) Try from a different browser/wallet client. (5) If all fails contact Moonsale support with your presale contract address.","tags":["finalization","creator","support","gas","error"]}
{"question":"transfer fee check testnet not applicable meaning","answer":"Transfer-tax behavior could not be reliably assessed in testnet mode for that scan.","tags":["scanner","testnet","security","creator"]}
{"question":"unlocked tokens within limit meaning in fair launch","answer":"After deposit, remaining wallet tokens must stay below platform max unlocked threshold.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","security","tokenomics"]}
{"question":"vesting says claimable 0 but cliff should be done by now","answer":"Verify vesting start, cliff end, and claim interval on-chain. If timing passed and still zero, contact support with vesting contract link.","tags":["vesting","cliff","claim","support","investor"]}
{"question":"vesting schedule can dev cancel it or not","answer":"That depends on vesting contract design. Review contract behavior and sale terms before investing.","tags":["vesting","security","investor","contracts"]}
{"question":"walk me through creating a presale step by step","answer":"1) Go to moonsale.app/create. 2) Paste your token address — the form auto-fills name/symbol. 3) Set token price, softcap, hardcap, min/max contribution, start/end time. 4) Set liquidity % (min 51%) and lock duration. 5) Optionally enable vesting. 6) Add project info (name, description, logo URL, socials). 7) Click Deploy and confirm 2 wallet txns. 8) Go to My Launches and pay the listing fee. Done!","tags":["presale","creator","onboarding","step_by_step"]}
{"question":"wats fair launch mean vs normal presale","answer":"Presale has fixed token rate and hardcap. Fair launch uses dynamic price discovery from total raised and token pool.","tags":["fair_launch","presale","price_discovery","investor"]}
{"question":"wats the max i can put in one presale","answer":"Maximum contribution is set per sale. Your wallet cannot exceed that configured max amount.","tags":["contribution","investor","presale","fair_launch"]}
{"question":"wats vesting mean in simple words","answer":"Vesting means your tokens unlock gradually over time instead of all at once.","tags":["vesting","investor","tokens"]}
{"question":"wen can i claim my tokens","answer":"Claim opens after successful finalization. If vesting exists, only currently unlocked portion is claimable.","tags":["claim","finalize","investor","vesting"]}
{"question":"wen does my next vesting unlock happen","answer":"Next unlock is determined by vesting start, cliff, and interval schedule in contract.","tags":["vesting","claim","cliff","investor"]}
{"question":"wen is final price decided","answer":"Final fair launch price is set at finalization using total raised and token pool.","tags":["fair_launch","finalize","price_discovery","investor"]}
{"question":"wen launch bro","answer":"Check exact start time and timezone on the sale countdown. If time passed and buy is still locked, verify chain, whitelist rules, and sale status.","tags":["status","presale","investor","support"]}
{"question":"wen moon","answer":"No one can guarantee profit timing. Focus on verified fundamentals like tokenomics, locks, vesting, and team quality.","tags":["risk","investor","general"]}
{"question":"what 4 more security score categories are planned but not yet scored","answer":"Max Wallet Unlock %, Contract Tax (buy+sell fee sum), Top 10 Holder Concentration, and Liquidity-to-Market-Cap Ratio. These aren't counted yet. When added, weights will be rebalanced to stay at exactly 50 total.","tags":["security_score","roadmap"]}
{"question":"what are all the fees I need to pay to launch a presale on moonsale","answer":"1) Token creation fee (if using Moonsale token generator). 2) Presale listing fee (paid from My Launches after deploy). 3) Platform fee % of raised funds (taken at finalization). 4) Token lock fee (if locking team tokens). 5) Vesting setup fee (if creating vesting schedules). 6) Gas fees for every transaction. Exact amounts shown on each tool page.","tags":["fees","creator","presale","onboarding","checklist"]}
{"question":"what are gas fees for presale deployment roughly","answer":"Depends on network congestion. On BSC gas is typically cheap (cents to low dollars). On ETH it can be significant (dollars to tens of dollars). Get test estimates by doing a testnet deploy first.","tags":["fees","gas","presale","creator","bnb","ethereum"]}
{"question":"what are min contribution and max contribution for","answer":"Min contribution stops people from spamming tiny amounts. Max contribution prevents one whale from buying the whole presale. Setting a reasonable max (like 2–5 BNB) distributes tokens more fairly, which also looks better to the community.","tags":["presale","contribution","creator","whitelist"]}
{"question":"what are the critical risk categories in the security score","answer":"Three of them: Liquidity Lock Duration, Team Token Lock, and Contract Verified on Explorer. If ANY of these scores 0 (Risky), a red 'Critical Risks Detected' banner shows on your sale page regardless of overall score. Even a 40+ total score means little with a critical risk banner.","tags":["security_score","critical_risk","lp_lock","token_lock","contract_verified","creator","investor"]}
{"question":"what are the softcap size category thresholds for BNB in the security score","answer":"≥50 BNB = full 1pt. 20–49 BNB = 0.67pt. 10–19 BNB = 0.33pt. Under 10 BNB = 0pts (Risky). For ETH equivalent thresholds may differ — check /security-score for exact values.","tags":["security_score","softcap","creator","bnb"]}
{"question":"what are the two transactions when I deploy a presale","answer":"First txn is approving the token spend (so the presale contract can pull your tokens). Second txn is the actual deployment of the presale contract. Both need to be confirmed in your wallet.","tags":["presale","creator","transactions","deploy"]}
{"question":"what can I do on the token management page at /token-management","answer":"Mainly for Liquidity Generator tokens — update fees (buy/sell), set/change your marketing wallet, toggle swap on/off, manage fee exclusions (exempt certain wallets from fees). Standard and other token types have fewer options there.","tags":["token_management","liquidity_generator","creator","fees","tools"]}
{"question":"what causes deploy failure during presale creation","answer":"Common causes are wrong chain, insufficient gas, rejected wallet confirmation, incomplete token approval, or invalid config outside platform limits.","tags":["presale","deploy","troubleshoot","creator"]}
{"question":"what decimals should I use for my token","answer":"18 is the standard for ERC-20 and what almost all projects use. Unless you have a specific reason to use different decimals, stick with 18.","tags":["token_creation","decimals","creator"]}
{"question":"what DEX does moonsale add liquidity to","answer":"PancakeSwap for BNB Chain, Uniswap for Ethereum. It happens automatically when you finalize. You don't manually add liquidity.","tags":["liquidity","dex","pancakeswap","uniswap","finalization","creator"]}
{"question":"what do I need ready before starting the create form","answer":"You need: a wallet with gas money, your token contract address, a tokenomics plan (how many tokens for presale vs liquidity vs team), sale start/end times, softcap amount, and your project info (logo URL, description, socials). Have all this ready before you hit deploy.","tags":["presale","creator","onboarding","checklist"]}
{"question":"what does change token button do in fair launch creator","answer":"It exits current token context so you can select a different token and rerun eligibility flow.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","token","support"]}
{"question":"what does cliff mean in vesting","answer":"After the TGE unlock, the cliff is a waiting period where NO additional tokens vest. The beneficiary already has their TGE tokens but can't claim more until the cliff period ends. After the cliff, linear vesting kicks in.","tags":["vesting","cliff","creator"]}
{"question":"what does draft saved start over mean","answer":"Draft data is stored temporarily, and Start over resets the form flow so you can rebuild settings.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","support"]}
{"question":"what does TGE mean","answer":"Token Generation Event — basically the start date of vesting when the initial % of tokens gets released immediately. On Moonsale presales, minimum TGE unlock is 20% of allocated tokens.","tags":["vesting","tge","creator"]}
{"question":"what does the max button on the presale rate field do","answer":"The Max button auto-fills the presale rate at the value that complies with the platform's minimum listing premium and uses 100% of your token supply allocation. It's a helper to quickly set a valid maximum rate.","tags":["presale","creator","rate","listing_premium","ui"]}
{"question":"what does the token scanner at /token-scanner check","answer":"It's an investor-facing tool to analyze any token contract for red flags. Things like honeypot detection, ownership status, buy/sell tax, blacklist functions, etc. Use it to check your own token before launch to spot any issues.","tags":["scanner","investor","creator","blacklist","tools"]}
{"question":"what does the vesting schedule detail page show","answer":"Progress bar showing % vested so far, live countdown to next milestone, three-milestone timeline (TGE date / Cliff ends / Fully Vested date), total amount, amount claimed, amount claimable now, and a Claim button.","tags":["vesting","investor","creator","ui"]}
{"question":"what does token failed eligibility check mean in fair launch","answer":"It means the eligibility scanner found a blocking condition that must be fixed before deployment.","tags":["fair_launch","scanner","security","creator"]}
{"question":"what does token ownership check amount mean","answer":"It shows your wallet token balance available for deposit and confirms ownership is detectable.","tags":["token","creator","fair_launch","scanner"]}
{"question":"what happens after deploy fair launch","answer":"Tokens are held in contract, investors contribute until end time, creator finalizes if softcap is met, liquidity is added at fair price, and investors claim instantly for no-vesting setup.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","finalize","liquidity","claim"]}
{"question":"what happens during finalization exactly","answer":"One transaction that: takes the raised BNB/ETH, adds liquidity % to PancakeSwap/Uniswap, locks the LP tokens for your set lock duration, and enables token claiming for investors. All automatic in one txn.","tags":["finalization","creator","lp_lock","liquidity","dex"]}
{"question":"what happens if moonsale goes down while my presale is active","answer":"Since everything is on-chain, your presale contract continues operating independently. Investors can't use the Moonsale UI but the contract is still there. Once Moonsale is back up everything resumes. This is the benefit of fully on-chain architecture.","tags":["presale","support","on_chain","downtime"]}
{"question":"what happens to tokens I put in the fair launch pool that nobody buys","answer":"If softcap is reached and you finalize, the token pool is split among contributors and the rest goes to liquidity at the final price. Fair launch uses all tokens in the pool for the price formula — there aren't really 'unsold' tokens the same way a presale has them.","tags":["fair_launch","token_pool","finalization","creator"]}
{"question":"what happens when the hardcap is hit","answer":"When the hardcap is reached the presale closes automatically — no more contributions accepted. Status changes to Filled. You then need to finalize it.","tags":["hardcap","presale","creator","finalization"]}
{"question":"what if I want to raise more than my hardcap because the presale is going great","answer":"You can't change the hardcap once deployed. The presale closes automatically when the hardcap is hit. If you want to raise more, plan a bigger hardcap from the start or do a separate second round.","tags":["hardcap","presale","creator","immutable"]}
{"question":"what if my presale fails because softcap is not reached","answer":"Investors get their refunds — they can claim directly from the contract anytime with no deadline. You get your deposited tokens back by withdrawing. The listing fee is gone. A soft fail is not catastrophic — learn from it and relaunch.","tags":["presale","softcap","refund","creator","failed"]}
{"question":"what if nobody contributes to my fair launch at all","answer":"If total raised is below softcap at end time, the sale fails. You can cancel and withdraw your deposited tokens back. No contributions = nothing lost for investors (they never sent anything).","tags":["fair_launch","softcap","cancel","refund","creator"]}
{"question":"what is a liquidity generator token","answer":"It's a token that charges a fee on every buy and sell. That fee gets split automatically between adding to the liquidity pool and sending to your marketing wallet. Popular for DeFi projects that want auto-liquidity. Comes with extra management options in the Token Management page.","tags":["token_creation","liquidity_generator","token","creator","defi"]}
{"question":"what is listing premium","answer":"The presale price should be at a discount vs the listing price — so investors get a better deal than people who buy after listing. The platform enforces a minimum listing premium to ensure investors are actually getting a presale benefit. The Max button on the rate field respects this.","tags":["presale","listing_premium","investor","creator"]}
{"question":"what is presale allocation percentage in the security score and how do I max it","answer":"It measures combined presale + liquidity tokens as a % of total supply. To get full 5pts you need ≥55% of your total supply going to presale + liquidity. So if total supply is 1B tokens, at least 550M should go to presale + liquidity combined.","tags":["security_score","presale_allocation","creator","liquidity"]}
{"question":"what is softcap and how do I pick the right number","answer":"Softcap is the minimum you need to raise for the presale to succeed. If you don't hit it, all investors get refunded. Pick a number you're confident you can actually reach — an ambitious softcap that fails is worse than a modest one that succeeds. Security Score gives full 1pt for softcap ≥ 50 BNB.","tags":["softcap","presale","creator","security_score","refund"]}
{"question":"what is the difference between /lock and /vesting for team tokens","answer":"/lock = all tokens locked until one date, released all at once. /vesting = tokens released gradually with TGE + cliff + linear schedule. Use lock for simpler 'team tokens locked for 1 year' situations. Use vesting for proper staged release schedules.","tags":["token_lock","vesting","creator","tools"]}
{"question":"what is the difference between presale and fair launch, which should I pick","answer":"Presale = fixed price you set, has a hardcap. Fair launch = no fixed price, price determined at the end based on total raised divided by token pool. Fair launch is good if you want community-driven price discovery. Presale is better if you want predictable raise amounts.","tags":["presale","fair_launch","creator","onboarding"]}
{"question":"what is the difference between token lock and vesting","answer":"Token Lock = tokens locked until a specific date, then ALL released at once. Vesting = tokens released gradually over time (TGE unlock + cliff + linear release). Use lock for simpler cases. Use vesting when you want staged gradual release.","tags":["token_lock","vesting","creator"]}
{"question":"what is the investors page at /investors for","answer":"It's a dedicated information hub for investors about the Moonsale platform. Separate from the investor docs — more of a landing page for investor-focused information.","tags":["investor","platform"]}
{"question":"what is the maximum vesting duration on moonsale","answer":"1825 days (5 years). The form shows a red error if you try to set more than that. Anything up to 5 years is valid.","tags":["vesting","creator","duration"]}
{"question":"what is the minimum liquidity percentage I can set","answer":"Minimum is 51% of raised funds must go to liquidity. The platform enforces this. But for a good Security Score you want ≥85% liquidity — that gets you full 5 points in that category.","tags":["liquidity","presale","creator","security_score"]}
{"question":"what is the minimum lock period on moonsale token lock tool","answer":"The platform has admin-enforced minimum lock days. Check the lock page for the current minimum — it should show before you confirm. Generally you want to lock for at least 180 days minimum for investor trust, 365+ for full Security Score points.","tags":["token_lock","lock_duration","creator","security_score"]}
{"question":"what is the minimum TGE unlock percentage for presale vesting","answer":"Minimum 20%. You can't set TGE below 20% in the presale vesting settings. Fair launches don't have built-in investor vesting at all.","tags":["vesting","tge","presale","creator"]}
{"question":"what is the moonsale buybot and how do I add it to my Telegram","answer":"MoonSale BuyBot is a Telegram bot at t.me/moonsale_buybot. It posts buy notifications in your group when someone buys your token. Helps build hype in your community. Add it to your Telegram group through the Telegram bot interface.","tags":["buybot","telegram","creator","marketing","tools"]}
{"question":"what is the security score on moonsale","answer":"It's an automatic score (out of 50) that rates every presale/fair launch across 11 categories. Investors use it to evaluate your project. Higher score = more trust. Scored using on-chain data + platform metadata. Shows on the Security tab of your sale page.","tags":["security_score","investor","creator","trust"]}
{"question":"what is the token management page for","answer":"It's mainly useful if you deployed a Liquidity Generator token. It shows extra panels where you can update buy/sell fees, set your marketing wallet address, toggle swapping on/off, and manage which addresses are excluded from fees. Standard tokens don't need much management from there.","tags":["token_management","liquidity_generator","creator","fees"]}
{"question":"what is the token price field — is it per token or per BNB","answer":"It's the cost of 1 token in BNB (or ETH). So if you set 0.0001 BNB per token, investors pay 0.0001 BNB for each token they receive. Keep it simple — calculate based on your desired FDV.","tags":["presale","token_price","creator"]}
{"question":"what is the total cost to launch a presale from scratch on BNB chain roughly","answer":"Rough ballpark on BSC: Token creation fee + Presale listing fee + Token lock fee (optional) + Gas for ~5 transactions. Probably 0.05–0.2 BNB total depending on current fee settings and gas prices. Check /fees for exact current numbers.","tags":["fees","creator","bnb","presale","onboarding"]}
{"question":"what score should I aim for","answer":"Aim for 40+/50 with no critical risks. 30+ with no critical risks is a reasonable baseline. Anything below 30 or with critical risks flagged will scare off serious investors. 50/50 is achievable if you tick all boxes.","tags":["security_score","investor","creator"]}
{"question":"what should i check before pressing deploy presale","answer":"Confirm token balance, rates, caps, min/max buy, liquidity and lock settings, timeline, vesting config, and project links. Keep enough native token for gas and listing fee.","tags":["presale","creator","deploy","checklist"]}
{"question":"what should I put in the lock title field","answer":"Put something descriptive like 'Team Allocation', 'Marketing Reserve', 'Advisor Tokens' so your community can tell which lock is which. Useful when you have multiple locks for the same token.","tags":["token_lock","creator"]}
{"question":"what token types can I create on moonsale","answer":"Four types: Standard (basic fixed supply ERC-20), Liquidity Generator (auto buy/sell fee split to LP + marketing wallet), Burnable (holders can burn their tokens), Mintable+Burnable (owner can mint new tokens AND holders can burn). Pick based on your project needs.","tags":["token_creation","token","creator"]}
{"question":"whats the moonsale buybot do exactly","answer":"MoonSale BuyBot posts real-time buy updates in Telegram for supported tokens.","tags":["buybot","telegram","tools","general"]}
{"question":"when do investors claim tokens in no vesting fair launch","answer":"After successful finalization, claims are available instantly in no-vesting configuration.","tags":["fair_launch","claim","investor","vesting"]}
{"question":"when I finalize a fair launch what exactly happens","answer":"Finalization locks the final price (total raised ÷ token pool), adds liquidity to Uniswap/PancakeSwap and locks the LP, and makes tokens claimable for all contributors. All happens in one transaction.","tags":["fair_launch","finalization","creator","liquidity","lp_lock"]}
{"question":"where can i review all fair launch values before deploy","answer":"Use the Review and Deploy step to verify token amounts, caps, liquidity, timing, whitelist mode, and fee notes before confirming.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","deploy","support"]}
{"question":"where do i add the token to my metamask after claim","answer":"In MetaMask use Import Tokens and paste the token contract address from the official sale page.","tags":["metamask","claim","wallet","support"]}
{"question":"where do i even find presales on this site","answer":"Browse launches at https://www.moonsale.app/presale","tags":["presale","browse","investor"]}
{"question":"where do I find all my locks and vesting schedules in one place","answer":"Token Lock → 'My Locks' section at /lock. Vesting → 'My Schedules' section at /vesting. Each shows cards for your active locks/schedules.","tags":["token_lock","vesting","creator","ui"]}
{"question":"where do I find my presale contract address to give to my auditor","answer":"After deploying, your sale page URL contains the contract address. Also check My Launches — click into your sale and the contract address should be visible, or find it via block explorer by looking at your wallet's transaction history for the deployment txn.","tags":["presale","contract_address","creator","audit","support"]}
{"question":"where do i see all my investments in one place","answer":"Use My Contributions or invested views to track joined sales, claim state, and refund status.","tags":["portfolio","investor","support","contribution"]}
{"question":"where do I see the moonsale changelog","answer":"No public changelog is visible on the site. The version number shows in the footer/sidebar. For updates follow Moonsale's official channels.","tags":["platform","support","changelog"]}
{"question":"where is the security score implementation source code","answer":"According to the docs, the implementation lives in apps/web/lib/securityScore.ts. The /security-score page is described as the canonical reference that stays in sync with the code.","tags":["security_score","developer","source_code"]}
{"question":"which chain dis on eth or bnb","answer":"MoonSale supports BNB Chain and Ethereum. Each sale runs on one chain, shown on the sale page.","tags":["chains","bnb","ethereum","investor"]}
{"question":"which chains does moonsale support","answer":"BNB Smart Chain and Ethereum mainnet. For testing you can use BNB Testnet and Sepolia. More chains are coming soon according to the homepage.","tags":["chains","bnb","ethereum","testnet","support"]}
{"question":"which project info links should i fill","answer":"Website, X, Telegram, and optional GitHub, Discord, and whitepaper should be filled with official links for better credibility.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","listing","marketing"]}
{"question":"whitelist full can i still apply","answer":"Whitelist changes are controlled by project team. Ask official project channels for updates.","tags":["whitelist","support","investor"]}
{"question":"whitelist open to everyone meaning","answer":"Sale is public, so any eligible wallet on correct chain can contribute.","tags":["fair_launch","whitelist","contribution","investor"]}
{"question":"whitelisted on bsc but want to contribute on eth is that possible","answer":"No. Whitelist and contribution are sale and chain specific. BSC and ETH launches are separate contracts.","tags":["whitelist","chains","bnb","ethereum","investor"]}
{"question":"who audited moonsale itself","answer":"MoonSale states its core contracts were independently audited before mainnet deployment. Use official docs for current audit references.","tags":["audit","security","contracts","general"]}
{"question":"who can see my vesting schedules","answer":"Both creator and beneficiary see their schedule cards in My Schedules at /vesting. Each schedule also has a shareable detail page with progress bar, countdown, and claim button. Anyone with the URL can view it.","tags":["vesting","creator","investor","visibility"]}
{"question":"who finalizes fair launch after softcap","answer":"Creator finalizes after sale end when softcap condition is met.","tags":["fair_launch","finalize","creator","softcap"]}
{"question":"why scanner shows ticks and arrows together","answer":"Ticks indicate passed checks; arrow-style indicators often show informational or not-applicable checks rather than hard failure.","tags":["scanner","support","security","creator"]}
{"question":"why should I lock team tokens, isn't my word enough","answer":"'Trust me bro' doesn't work in crypto. On-chain locks are verifiable proof. Investors can check the unlock date themselves without trusting your word. It's the strongest trust signal you can give besides KYC.","tags":["token_lock","trust","creator","investor","security_score"]}
{"question":"why total deposit is less than full supply","answer":"Because a small amount remains unlocked in wallet by design, as long as it stays within platform unlocked limit.","tags":["fair_launch","creator","tokenomics","security"]}
{"question":"why was this blocked dex pair reserves pair has existing liquidity","answer":"This token already has liquidity in an existing DEX pair. Launching another initial pool would create extraction risk, so deployment is blocked.","tags":["fair_launch","liquidity","dex","security","creator"]}
{"question":"wrong network showing wht do i do","answer":"Switch wallet to the chain used by the sale, then refresh and reconnect.","tags":["wallet","chains","support","metamask"]}
